                <h1>Empowering Women: Explore the Women's Rights Movement</h1>
                <p>The women's rights movement has been a pivotal force in advocating for gender equality, promoting women's legal and social rights. It emerged in the late 19th century, addressing issues like suffrage, education, and workplace rights. The movement has evolved, continuously fighting against discrimination and striving for equal opportunities globally.</p>
